  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>The Enchanted Forest</h1>
      <p>A world where kindness is the strongest thing there is</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ====== WELCOME INTRO ====== -->
  <section class="section world-intro">
    <div class="container container--narrow text-center">
      <div class="fade-in">
        <h2>Welcome to the Forest</h2>
        <p style="font-size: 1.1rem; line-height: 1.8;">Welcome to the enchanted forest, a story world where kindness still matters, quiet courage has power, and even the smallest spark of light can help guide the way. This is the place where Norbert's deeper stories live, among listening trees, hidden paths, ravens, fairies, and creatures who carry lessons in their footsteps.</p>
        <p style="font-size: 1.1rem; line-height: 1.8;">These stories are written for children, but they often meet the grown-up heart too. In the enchanted forest, grief is held gently, courage grows in tender ways, and healing comes through presence, friendship, and truth. It is a world meant to comfort, awaken wonder, and help people feel less alone.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ====== CHARACTERS ====== -->
  <section class="section" style="background: var(--cream-warm);">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="text-center fade-in">
        <h2>Who Lives Here</h2>
        <p class="section-subtitle">The hearts of the enchanted forest</p>
      </div>
      <div class="characters-grid">
        <div class="character-card fade-in">
          <div class="character-avatar">
            <img src="images/norbert-character.jpg" alt="Norbert Barkah portrait, smiling" style="width: 100%; height: 100%; object-fit: cover; object-position: center 20%; border-radius: 50%;">
          </div>
          <h3>Norbert</h3>
          <p>Norbert Barkah is the gentle heart of the forest. Wise, loyal, and deeply feeling, he moves through the world with quiet presence and a kindness that helps others feel safe enough to grow.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="character-card fade-in">
          <div class="character-avatar">
            <img src="images/lyra-character.jpg" alt="Lyra the fairy, watercolor illustration by Susan Higgins" style="width: 100%; height: 100%; object-fit: cover; border-radius: 50%;">
          </div>
          <h3>Lyra</h3>
          <p>Lyra is a tiny fairy whose light awakens through true kindness. Soft, perceptive, and lantern-like in spirit, she helps reveal the deeper meaning inside each story and reminds readers that inner light is something we grow by how we love.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="character-card fade-in">
          <div class="character-avatar">
            <img src="images/sophia-character.jpg" alt="Sophia the Hedge Witch" style="width: 100%; height: 100%; object-fit: cover; border-radius: 50%;">
          </div>
          <h3>Sophia</h3>
          <p>Sophia brings an older, earth-wise presence to the story world. She carries mystery, depth, and the feeling that the forest holds ancient knowing for those willing to listen. Her presence widens the world and hints at the many layers still waiting to be explored.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ====== THEMES ====== -->
  <section class="section story-world">
    <div class="container text-center">
      <h2 class="fade-in">What the Forest Teaches</h2>
      <p class="section-subtitle fade-in">The truths that run through every story</p>
      <div class="world-features">
        <div class="world-feature fade-in">
          <span class="feature-icon">&#127807;</span>
          <h3>Kindness as Strength</h3>
          <p>In this world, kindness is not weakness. It is a living force that changes outcomes, heals wounds, and lights the path forward.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="world-feature fade-in">
          <span class="feature-icon">&#128156;</span>
          <h3>Courage in Tender Steps</h3>
          <p>Courage does not always roar here. Sometimes it is the next breath, the honest feeling, or the gentle choice to keep going.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="world-feature fade-in">
          <span class="feature-icon">&#10024;</span>
          <h3>Inner Light and Healing</h3>
          <p>These stories help readers remember that even in fear, sorrow, or confusion, there is light within that can steady the heart and guide the next step.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ====== CTA ====== -->
  <section class="section" style="background: var(--cream);">
    <div class="container container--narrow text-center">
      <div class="fade-in">
        <h2>Step Inside</h2>
        <p style="font-size: 1.1rem;">The enchanted forest is always here. Start with a story, follow where it leads, and see what you find.</p>
        <div style="display: flex; gap: 1rem; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap; margin-top: 1.5rem;">
          <a href="books.html" class="btn btn--primary">Read the Books</a>
